<body>
  <header class="header">
    <div class="header-content">
      <div class="logo">
        <div class="logo-badge">
          <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i>
        </div>
        <span>Backup Client</span>
      </div>
      <nav class="nav-links">
        <a href="/" class="nav-link">
          <i class="fas fa-home"></i>
          Dashboard
        </a>
        <a href="/settings" class="nav-link">
          <i class="fas fa-cog"></i>
          Settings
        </a>
        <a href="/logs" class="nav-link">
          <i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i>
          Logs
        </a>
        <a href="/help" class="nav-link active">
          <i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i>
          Help
        </a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Help & Documentation</h1>
      <p>Everything you need to know about using the Backup Client</p>
    </div>

    <!-- What is This? -->
    <div class="help-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        <div class="section-icon"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i></div>
        What is the Backup Client?
      </h2>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        The Backup Client is a simple program that automatically copies your important files to a safe location (backup server). 
        Think of it like making a copy of your photos, documents, and other files so that if something happens to your computer, 
        you won't lose them. It works quietly in the background and can run automatically at times you choose.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Features Explained -->
    <div class="help-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        <div class="section-icon"><i class="fas fa-star"></i></div>
        Features Explained (In Simple Terms)
      </h2>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-play-circle"></i></div>
          <div class="feature-content">
            <h3>Manual Backup</h3>
            <p>
              <strong>What it does:</strong> Copies your files right now when you click the "Backup Now" button.<br>
              <strong>When to use:</strong> When you want to make a backup immediately, like after working on important documents.<br>
              <strong>How to use:</strong> Go to Dashboard → Click "Backup Now" button → Wait for it to finish.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-clock"></i></div>
          <div class="feature-content">
            <h3>Automatic Backup</h3>
            <p>
              <strong>What it does:</strong> Automatically backs up your files at specific times (like 2 AM every day) without you doing anything.<br>
              <strong>When to use:</strong> For regular, worry-free backups while you sleep or when you're not using the computer.<br>
              <strong>How to use:</strong> Go to Settings → Enable "Automatic Backups" → Choose times → Save.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-folder"></i></div>
          <div class="feature-content">
            <h3>Backup Sources</h3>
            <p>
              <strong>What it does:</strong> Tells the program which folders you want to backup.<br>
              <strong>Examples:</strong> Your Documents folder, Pictures folder, or any folder with important files.<br>
              <strong>How to use:</strong> Go to Settings → Click "Add Folder" → Type the folder path → Save.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-ban"></i></div>
          <div class="feature-content">
            <h3>File Exclusions</h3>
            <p>
              <strong>What it does:</strong> Skips certain files or folders that you don't want to backup.<br>
              <strong>Examples:</strong> Temporary files, system files, or very large folders you don't need backed up.<br>
              <strong>Note:</strong> Common exclusions (like temporary internet files) are already pre-configured for you.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-server"></i></div>
          <div class="feature-content">
            <h3>Server Connection</h3>
            <p>
              <strong>What it does:</strong> Connects to the computer that stores your backups.<br>
              <strong>Think of it like:</strong> The address of the safe where your backup copies are stored.<br>
              <strong>How to use:</strong> Usually pre-configured by your IT person or tech support. You can test it by clicking the "Test" button.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i></div>
          <div class="feature-content">
            <h3>Logs</h3>
            <p>
              <strong>What it does:</strong> Keeps a record of all backups - what was backed up, when, and if there were any problems.<br>
              <strong>When to use:</strong> To check if your backups are working correctly or to troubleshoot issues.<br>
              <strong>How to use:</strong> Go to Dashboard → Click "View Logs" → See the history.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Getting Started -->
    <div class="help-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        <div class="section-icon"><i class="fas fa-rocket"></i></div>
        Getting Started (First Time Setup)
      </h2>
      <div class="step-list">
        <div class="step-item">
          <div class="step-number">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Add Folders to Backup</h4>
            <p>Go to Settings and click "Add Folder". Type in the folders you want to protect, like C:\Users\YourName\Documents</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step-item">
          <div class="step-number">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Test Your First Backup</h4>
            <p>Go back to Dashboard and click "Backup Now" to make sure everything works. This might take a few minutes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step-item">
          <div class="step-number">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Enable Automatic Backups</h4>
            <p>In Settings, turn on "Enable Automatic Backups" and choose when you want backups to run (we recommend 2:00 AM).</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step-item">
          <div class="step-number">4</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h4>Set Up Auto-Start (Optional)</h4>
            <p>Click the button below to learn how to make the backup program start automatically when Windows starts.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <a href="/setup-windows" class="btn btn-block">
          <i class="fab fa-windows"></i>
          Setup Automatic Startup on Windows
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="help-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        <div class="section-icon"><i class="fas fa-question"></i></div>
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>

      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem;">
        <div>
          <h3 style="color: var(--slate-900); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">❓ How long does a backup take?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-600);">It depends on how many files you have. The first backup might take a while (30 minutes to a few hours), but after that, only new or changed files are backed up, which is usually very quick (a few minutes).</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 style="color: var(--slate-900); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">❓ Can I use my computer while it's backing up?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-600);">Yes! The backup runs in the background. You might notice your computer is slightly slower if you're backing up very large files.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 style="color: var(--slate-900); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">❓ What happens if my computer shuts down during a backup?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-600);">Don't worry! The backup will automatically resume from where it left off the next time it runs. You won't lose any data.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 style="color: var(--slate-900); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">❓ How do I know if my backups are working?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-600);">Check the Dashboard. It shows your last backup time and recent activity. You can also click "View Logs" to see detailed history.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 style="color: var(--slate-900); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">❓ What should I backup?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-600);">Focus on irreplaceable files: Documents, Photos, Videos, Music, and any work files. You don't need to backup programs or system files.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 style="color: var(--slate-900); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">❓ Can I restore my files if something goes wrong?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-600);">Yes! Contact your IT support or check the main backup server website to download your backed-up files.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Tips -->
    <div class="help-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        <div class="section-icon"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i></div>
        Helpful Tips
      </h2>

      <div class="tip-box">
        <div class="tip-icon"><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="font-size: 1.5rem;"></i></div>
        <div>
          <strong>Schedule backups at night:</strong> Set automatic backups for 2:00 AM or 3:00 AM so they don't slow down your computer during the day.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tip-box">
        <div class="tip-icon"><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="font-size: 1.5rem;"></i></div>
        <div>
          <strong>Leave your computer on:</strong> For automatic backups to work, your computer needs to be on (you can let it go to sleep, but don't shut it down).
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tip-box">
        <div class="tip-icon"><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="font-size: 1.5rem;"></i></div>
        <div>
          <strong>Check logs weekly:</strong> Take a quick look at the logs once a week to make sure your backups are running successfully.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tip-box">
        <div class="tip-icon"><i class="fas fa-check-circle" style="font-size: 1.5rem;"></i></div>
        <div>
          <strong>Run manual backup before big changes:</strong> Before updating Windows or installing new software, run a manual backup first.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Need More Help -->
    <div class="help-section" style="text-align: center;">
      <h2 class="section-title" style="justify-content: center;">
        <div class="section-icon"><i class="fas fa-life-ring"></i></div>
        Need More Help?
      </h2>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        If you're still having trouble or have questions, don't hesitate to ask for help!
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/" class="btn">
          <i class="fas fa-home"></i>
          Back to Dashboard
        </a>
        <a href="/setup-windows" class="btn">
          <i class="fab fa-windows"></i>
          Windows Setup Guide
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
